---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Laos Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/laos/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Vietnam for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/vietnam' },
  { title: 'Cambodia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/cambodia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'laosFit', header: 'Laos Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'LAK$7.5M-10.7M/mo', laosFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'LAK$8.8M-12.5M/mo', laosFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'LAK$6.7M-9.6M/mo', laosFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'LAK$6.3M-8.9M/mo', laosFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Pacific Cross', entryAge: '70', renewal: 'To 99', monthlyFrom: 'LAK$4.5M-7.0M/mo', laosFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'LAK$6.7M-10.7M', annual: 'LAK$80M-128M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'LAK$9.2M-14.2M', annual: 'LAK$110M-171M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'LAK$12.4M-19.1M', annual: 'LAK$149M-229M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'LAK$300K-800K/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Thailand Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'LAK$50M-150M' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Laos 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Laos. Laid-back lifestyle, affordable living, French colonial charm, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Laos"
  subheadline="Laos offers supremely laid-back lifestyle, stunning natural beauty, French colonial remnants, Buddhist culture, and extremely affordable living—Southeast Asia's sleepy alternative to Thailand."
  heroImage="/images/countries/laos-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Laos</h2>
  <p>
    Laos offers what Thailand had decades ago—unhurried pace, genuine smiles, Buddhist temples, French baguettes, affordable living, and natural beauty without mass tourism. For those seeking escape from modern rush and willing to accept limited healthcare, Laos delivers authentic experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Vientiane is the sleepy capital with best services. Luang Prabang (UNESCO) offers spiritual beauty and expat community. Vang Vieng has backpacker-turned-resort atmosphere. Southern Laos has 4000 Islands relaxation. Most retirees choose Vientiane or Luang Prabang for services.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; Thailand evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Lao; French remnants; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> LAK$12M-25M/month (~$600-1,250 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; hot; rainy season May-Oct</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Laid-back; Buddhist; French influence</li>
      <li><strong>Thailand border:</strong> 1-hour to Thai hospitals</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Laos Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Laos healthcare is very limited—local facilities handle only basic care. Mahosot Hospital and French Embassy Clinic in Vientiane are best options. Most serious conditions require evacuation to Thailand. Udon Thani (1 hour from Vientiane) and Bangkok (1 hour flight) are common destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is basic. Private options limited even in Vientiane. Thailand provides essential medical backup. Many expats cross to Thailand regularly for healthcare. International insurance with Thailand coverage is non-negotiable.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Thailand Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Laos cannot treat most serious conditions. Udon Thani, Thailand is 1 hour from Vientiane by road; Bangkok is 1-hour flight. Plan for Thailand healthcare—Laos is your home, Thailand is your hospital. Insurance must cover Thai treatment.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Laos has limited long-term options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-day visa on arrival for most nationalities. Extensions to 60 days possible. Border runs common for extended stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Visa (B2)</h3>
  <p>
    Multiple-entry option. Some semi-retired professionals use this route. Renewable in-country.
  </p>

  <h3>Non-Immigrant Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For family or investment purposes. Various categories with specific requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Limited formal retirement visa program. Check current requirements—policies evolve.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Laos:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> No insurance required for visa</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage absolutely essential</li>
    <li><strong>Thailand:</strong> Must include Thai hospital coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> To Bangkok/Udon Thani critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Laos</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with excellent Thailand coverage is non-negotiable. Most healthcare will happen in Thailand. Ensure evacuation to Bangkok included. Pacific Cross offers good Southeast Asia regional coverage. Don't skimp—Laos healthcare limitations are real.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Laos, Thailand coverage essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Laos</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Thailand network, excellent regional</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Pacific Cross:</strong> Southeast Asia specialist</li>
    <li><strong>Bangkok hospitals:</strong> Your specialists will be here</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with strong Thailand access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Laos (LAK ~20,000 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Don't cut Thailand:</strong> This is essential, not optional</li>
    <li><strong>Vientiane location:</strong> Closest to Thai border</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Pacific Cross offers value</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive care:</strong> Thailand routine checkups</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Escapist, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Tourist visa rotation. Luang Prabang.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Southeast Asia focus. Bangkok backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~LAK$7.5M/month (~$375). Simple living; Thai healthcare access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: French Francophone, 69</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month pension. Long-stay visa. Vientiane.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CFE + Pacific Cross regional. French connection.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~LAK$6.5M/month (~$325). Colonial nostalgia; regional coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Australian Wanderer, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> A$2,800/month pension. Visa rotation. Vang Vieng.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Asia-Pacific coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~LAK$10M/month (~$500). Adventure retirement; global backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Laos healthcare really that limited?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Laos cannot treat most serious conditions. Basic care only. Anything complex goes to Thailand. Udon Thani is 1 hour from Vientiane; Bangkok is 1-hour flight. Plan accordingly—this is real limitation, not exaggeration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is there a retirement visa?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Limited—Laos doesn't have clear retirement visa like Thailand. Most use tourist visa rotations or business visas. Some find long-term arrangements. Not as straightforward as neighboring countries. Research current options.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Laos over Thailand?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Laos is what Thailand was decades ago—slower, quieter, less developed, more authentic feel. Lower cost. Fewer tourists. Trade-off is healthcare limitations. Some prefer this simplicity; others need Thailand's infrastructure. Personal preference.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Laos safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—low crime. Buddhist culture is peaceful. UXO (unexploded ordnance) exists in rural areas from Vietnam War era—stick to cleared paths. Cities are safe. Overall peaceful destination. Different risks than crime-related.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Laos coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Lao authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
